body:
Hi!

My code looks like:

```csharp
SK3dView v = new SK3dView();
v.Translate(10, 10, 0); //x10, y10, z0
using (SKCanvas canvas = surface.Canvas) {
  canvas.SetMatrix(v.Matrix);
  canvas.DrawRect(new SKRect(0, 0, 100, 100), new SKPaint() { 
    Color = new SKColor(255, 0, 0), 
    IsAntialias = true, });
}
```

Now the painted rectangle is not on the position x[10], y[10] (as I would expect it), its is on the position x[10], y[-10].
Is this a correct behavior?


EDIT:
The Z-Axis has the same behavior. A negative value makes the rectangle appear greater and a positive value makes the rectangle appear smaller.

Best regards,
Sora
